   Payton v. Woodford, 00-99000 / 00-99003
   Three-Judge Panel Opinion: 258 F.3d 905 (9th Cir. 2001)
   Order Taking Case En Banc: 273 F.3d 1271 (9th Cir. 2001)
   Date of Order Taking Case En Banc: December 19, 2001
   Status: Calendared March 20, 2002, 11:00 a.m., Phoenix
   Members of En Banc Court: Not yet available
   Issue(s): Death penalty case. Did the state prosecutor's incorrect
   statement to the jury -- that it could not legally consider mitigating
   evidence -- so infect the penalty phase of Payton's trial with
   unfairness that his resulting death sentence violated his due process
   rights?
   Holding: Not yet decided
     __________________________________________________________________

