   Aguirre-Cervantes v. INS, 99-70861
   Three-Judge Panel Opinion: 242 F.3d 1169 (9th Cir. 2001)
   Order Taking Case En Banc: 270 F.3d 794 (9th Cir. 2001)
   Date of Order Taking Case En Banc: October 23, 2001
   Status: Taken off calendar. Order entered by Chief Judge Schroeder,
   pursuant to the parties' stipulation, vacating the three-judge panel
   opinion and remanding to the BIA for the stipulated reopening of
   administrative proceedings.
   Order Vacating Panel Opinion: 273 F.3d 1220 (9th Cir. 2001)
   Date of Order Vacating Panel Opinion: December 7, 2001
   Issue(s): Could a family of children subjected to severe abuse by their
   father qualify as a particular social group for asylum purposes? Would
   any reasonable factfinder conclude from the evidence in this case that
   the Mexican government was unable or unwilling to control the father's
   abusive behavior? Can domestic violence constitute persecution under
   the immigration laws?
